[h3 id=Introduction 
	"Introduction
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Circuit Puzzle is a 2020 Uzebox puzzle game developed by Artcfox based on a physical board game. The goal is to complete a circuit by connecting the pieces such that there's no loose ends except at switches and the ground "-" piece. There's 60 puzzle to complete which this TAS completes in a little over 10 minutes.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The developer's website: 
	[a href=https://sites.google.com/site/artcfox/ rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"https://sites.google.com/site/artcfox/
	]a
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Uzebox wiki page: 
	[a href=https://uzebox.org/wiki/Circuit_Puzzle rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"https://uzebox.org/wiki/Circuit_Puzzle
	]a
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"As "research" for the All Platforms Challenge, I played a fair amount of RetroAchievements sets for Uzebox games. Circuit Puzzle was a cute game and it didn't seem too hard to make a TAS. For the most part this is straightforward but there's a couple of quirks to note.
	$LF
]div
