[h3 id=ExtraNotes 
	"Extra notes
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"For some reason the cursor has a small amount of inertia. This does make cursor movement a little tricky but nothing that can't be worked with.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Generally, the last piece placed was usually the ones that need to be placed at the top of the screen away from the lower piece bin. This isn't always the case since at the start of every puzzle the cursor sits on top of the top left piece. Sometimes this piece is one that needs to be placed at the top of the screen which means sometimes the last piece needs to be the second closest to the top of the screen.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Some set circuit pieces can be rotated but not moved. These are usually rotated while returning from placing a circuit piece onto the main board. There's a couple of puzzles where the rotation of some set circuit pieces is done after placing the remaining pieces due to no convenient route to get them along the way.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=PossibleImprovements 
	"Possible improvements
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"I did this TAS all by hand so there's a good chance that I might miss some small movement optimizations. I do think on a macro level that there might be faster circuit piece placement orders to consider but I didn't write a script to figure out that since the extra requirement of needing to rotate set circuit pieces makes the routing tricky to begin with.
	$LF
]div
